JCI commented that since the CVP tests proposed in AHRI 210/240 are complex and time consuming, it is crucial for laboratories under the AHRI audit program to put in place tolerances that are achievable. (JCI, No. 35 at p. 3) JCI requested that DOE delay CVP enforcement testing until sufficient CVP test data has been collected by labs to establish such tolerances. (
Id.
